==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Named after [[w:Julius Caesar|Julius Caesar]] who introduced the calendar in 46 B.C.
===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[Julian]] [[calendar]]|-}}
# The [[calendar]] which was used in the [[western world]] before the present-day [[Gregorian calendar]].  The Julian calendar differed in having all multiple-of-4 [[year]]s as [[leap year]]s.
